cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a novel unsupervised clustering framework that integrates several techniques from machine learning and computer vision, such as concept factorization, local-coordinate coding, and adaptive weighting. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the sub-categories of Machine Learning (cs.LG), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS), and Multimedia (cs.MM). Among these, cs.LG and cs.CV are the most likely categories, as the paper focuses on improving the representation ability of concept factorization for clustering high-dimensional data, which is a common problem in both machine learning and computer vision.
